-- Sappi CEO Boettger Says Pulp Prices to Drop `Gradually' Over Next 6 Months
-- Nicky Smith
-- 2010-08-02T07:45:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/sappi-ceo-boettger-says-pulp-prices-to-drop-gradually-over-next-6-months.html

          
          
             Sappi Ltd., the world’s largest maker
of glossy paper used in magazines, expects  pulp prices will
drop gradually as demand “softens,” Chief Executive Officer
Ralph Boettger said on a conference call with reporters.  
 Pulp prices may fall between $50 and $100 a metric ton over
the next six months, he said today on a call from Johannesburg.  
